HEADWORD: Sulphophosphorous
<hw>Sul`pho*phos"phor*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, a
hypothetical acid of phosphorus, analogous to phosphorous acid, and
known in its salts.</def>⟦br⟧
